<DocsLayout title="Getting Started">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  
  <p class="lead">
    Install zen and write your first skill in under 5 minutes.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  
  <pre><code class="language-bash">npm install zen-lang</code></pre>
  
  <p>Or with your preferred package manager:</p>
  
  <pre><code class="language-bash">pnpm add zen-lang
yarn add zen-lang</code></pre>

  <h2>Your First Skill</h2>
  
  <p>
    Create a file named <code>greeting.zen.md</code>:
  </p>
  
  <pre><code>---
name: greeting
description: When you need to greet someone
---

## Types

$Greeting = a friendly greeting message
$Name = person's name

## Input

- $name: $Name

## Workflow

1. Generate a $Greeting for $name
2. Make it appropriately warm and friendly
3. Return the greeting</code></pre>

  <h2>Compile Your Skill</h2>
  
  <pre><code class="language-bash">zen compile greeting.zen.md -o greeting.out.md</code></pre>
  
  <p>This produces a compiled skill with expanded types and transformed markers.</p>

  <h2>Validate Without Compiling</h2>
  
  <pre><code class="language-bash">zen check greeting.zen.md</code></pre>

  <h2>Use Programmatically</h2>
  
  <pre><code class="language-typescript">import &#123; parse, compile &#125; from 'zen-lang';

// Parse to AST
const ast = parse(source);
console.log(ast.frontmatter?.name);

// Compile to LLM-ready format
const result = compile(source);
console.log(result.output);
console.log(result.stats);</code></pre>

